littlefs-rust-core (v0.1.0, vendored with local patch)
================================================================================
Location:    third_party/littlefs-rust-core/
License:     BSD-3-Clause
Copyright:   littlefs-rust contributors
Upstream:    https://github.com/light-player/littlefs-rust

Pure-Rust port of littlefs, used as the block-level implementation behind the
`littlefs-rust` crate. Vendored locally with a single-line patch to
`lfs_alignup` in src/util.rs: upstream uses checked arithmetic that panics on
u32 overflow in Rust debug builds, while the C original and the rest of lfs
rely on unsigned wrap. The patch switches that site to wrapping_add /
wrapping_sub. This vendored copy retains its upstream BSD-3-Clause license;
it is not relicensed under GPL-3.0. BSD-3-Clause is GPL-3.0 compatible.

